8. Storage in Modern Systems
In contemporary computing environments, storage is deeply integrated with cloud computing, virtualization, and distributed systems. Cloud providers offer scalable storage services that abstract underlying hardware complexities, allowing users to provision storage on demand.
Virtualization enables multiple logical storage units to share physical resources, improving utilization and flexibility. Meanwhile, distributed storage systems spread data across multiple nodes, ensuring scalability and fault tolerance.
These advancements address the growing demand for data-intensive applications, including artificial intelligence, analytics, and global-scale web services.
